# Advanced Logic

Advanced Logic is a core feature of VariantalX that enables complex execution paths, adaptive runtime behavior, and variant-based processing.

---

## Variant Branching

Variant Branching allows a program to execute different logic depending on active variants.

```vx id="8vwyjt"
variant<1> {

    print<"Standard Mode">;

}

variant<2> {

    print<"Enhanced Mode">;

}
```

---

## Dynamic Variant Selection

Variants can be selected during runtime.

```vx id="t2l7sa"
currentVariant = runtime.detectVariant();

execute<currentVariant>;
```

---

## Conditional Chains

Multiple conditions can be linked together.

```vx id="nib1dq"
if playerVerified
    => loadProfile
    => generateSession
    => initializeRuntime;
```

---

## Runtime Switching

Execution paths may be altered while a program is running.

```vx id="x9mq5o"
runtime.switchVariant<5>;
```

---

## Logic Nodes

Logic Nodes are reusable execution units.

```vx id="urxkt8"
node GeneratePlayer {

    api.setPlayerId;

}
```

Execute:

```vx id="m8v6qe"
run<GeneratePlayer>;
```

---

## Adaptive Processing

Adaptive Processing changes behavior based on user state.

```vx id="e1jmb9"
if userFirstExperience{FE} {

    setNumberVariants<>2;

} else {

    setNumberVariants<>7;

}
```

---

## Advanced Example

```vx id="h6t9cw"
api.setPlayerId<
    numberVariation=[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,0]
>;

if userFirstExperience{FE} {

    runtime.switchVariant<2>;

    execute<Onboarding>;

} else {

    runtime.switchVariant<7>;

    execute<StandardSession>;

}
```

---

## VX-Advanced Recommendations

* Limit nested variants to 3 levels.
* Reuse Logic Nodes whenever possible.
* Keep runtime switching predictable.
* Avoid conflicting variant assignments.

---



Advanced Logic is available in VariantalX Runtime v2.0 and later.
